# Naming Conventions

**Import propagation:** Renaming files, modules, or public symbols requires updating all downstream `import` statements in the same change.

## Files

| Location | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Analysis scripts | `utils_anal/export_<what>.py` or `utils_anal/<what>_tuning.py` | `export_gate_avg.py`, `hidden_unit_tuning.py` |
| Visualisation scripts | `utils_viz/<what>.py` | `gate_avg_allsector.py`, `cnn_channel.py` |
| Paper figures | `utils_viz/paper_figs/<fig_id>.py` | `fig1.py` |
| Checkpoints | `results/train_data/<suffix>/<model>_<mode>_<hparams>_model.pth` | `gawf_sector_acc_h256_lr0.0005_wd0.0001_cdo0_rdo0.5_dz32_fb50_model.pth` |
| Analysis data | `results/anal_data/<module>/<descriptor>_<tag>.npy` | `avg_outer_ih_allcomp_sector3_space.npy` |
| Analysis figures | `results/anal_figs/<module>/<mode><idx>_<agg>_<descriptor>.png` | `sector3_space_avg_gate_allcomp.png` |
| Metadata JSON | `results/anal_data/<module>/<descriptor>_meta_<tag>.json` | `avg_gate_meta_allcomp_sector3_space.json` |
| Generalization launchers | `experiments/generalization/<phase>_<...>.sh` | `phase1_gawf_search.sh`, `phase2_lr_check.sh`, `phase3_train_scale.sh`, `run_all_scales_2gpu.sh` (`[short\|full]`, default short) |
| Generalization aggregation | `experiments/generalization/collect_results.py` | Subcommands: `phase1`, `phase1_short`, `emit_hparams_shared`, `phase2`, `phase3`, `phase3_import` |
| Full-grid hparam utility | `experiments/generalization/hparam_full_grid.py` | Subcommands: `emit-task`, `validate`, `status`, `summarize` |
| Amarel launchers | `experiments/amarel/*hparam_full_grid*.sh` | `submit_hparam_full_grid_batches.sh`, `rerun_hparam_full_grid_failed.sh` |
| Amarel smoke-test launchers | `experiments/amarel/*hparam_4h_5epoch_test*.sh` | 4h-only, 5-epoch hparam submission/status check |
| Amarel probe | `experiments/amarel/probe_amarel_slurm_limits.sh` | Slurm `sbatch --test-only` probe |
| Local hparam launchers | `experiments/local/*hparam*.sh` | `run_hparam_full_grid_2gpu.sh --scale 4`, local 2-GPU runs |
| Generalization tables | `experiments/generalization/artifacts/phase3_summary_<scale>.csv` | Optional **`_short`**: `phase3_summary_4h_short.csv` |
| Generalization hparams JSON | `experiments/generalization/artifacts/phase1_best.json`, `phase2_final_hparams.json` | Short variants: `*_short.json`; full-grid best: `gen_hparam_full_grid/hparam_best.json` |
| Generalization figures | `results/anal_figs/generalization/<metric>_vs_scale[ _short].{pdf,png}` | `overfit_gap_vs_scale`, `train_acc_vs_scale`, `val_acc_vs_scale` |
| Generalization plot entry | `utils_viz/plot_generalization.py` | Flags: `--artifact_dir`, `--csv_tag`, `--out_dir`, `--save-pdf` |

## Training engine functions (`utils/train_rnn_engine.py`)

Use these public names in new code (do not reintroduce old aliases):

| Function | Role |
|----------|------|
| `setup_training_components` | Build `components` for the whole run |
| `begin_epoch` | Start one training epoch (tqdm, online accumulators) |
| `train_batch` | Single training step |
| `summarize_online_train` | Log-only summary from online batch stats |
| `eval_train_subset` | Fair eval on train-eval subset loader → `train_*` arrays |
| `eval_valid` | Fair eval on validation loader → `val_*` arrays |
| `evaluate_epoch` | Low-level full pass on any `DataLoader` (eval mode) |
| `cleanup_dataloaders`, `stop_requested` | Shutdown / signal |

Symmetry: `eval_train_subset(mdl, components, epoch_ctx)` and `eval_valid(mdl, components, epoch_ctx, val_every=...)`.

## `train_helpers` helper classes (`utils/train_helpers.py`)

- **`LoggingHelper`** — `setup_logger`, `log_experiment_config`, `log_experiment_start`, `log_write`, `log_dataset_and_batch_info`; constant `BANNER_LEN` (same value as `LoggingHelper.BANNER_LEN`).
- **`PathHelper`** — `get_base_path`, `prepare_data_paths`, `load_raw_data`, `save_results`, `save_metrics_summary` (and private `_load_train_val`, `_load_single_split`). Do not use removed module-level wrappers for these.
- **`SummaryStatsHelper`** — `as_array_or_none`, `safe_max`, `safe_min`, `safe_last`, `safe_best_epoch_1based`, `gap`, `round2`; used by `summarize_experiment_metrics`.

## Variables

### Python
- **Functions:** `snake_case` verbs — `compute_activations`, `build_test_dataset`
- **Classes:** `PascalCase` — `GaWFRNNConv`, `AccelerationConfig`, `SingleCharMetricsMode`
- **Constants:** `UPPER_SNAKE` — `PROJECT_ROOT`, `BANNER_LEN`
- **Private helpers:** single underscore prefix — `_agg_ih`, `_draw_boundaries`
- **Loop index variables:** `sidx` (sample), `t` (time), `b` (batch), `d` (digit/component), `c` (channel)
- **Array shape variables:** `B` (batch), `T` (time/frames), `C` (channels), `H` (hidden or height), `W` (width)

### Tensor / Array Naming
| Name | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `frames` | input stimulus tensor `(B, T, C, H, W)` |
| `labels` | label tensor/array `(B, T, 2)` int64 in sector mode |
| `x_encoded` | CNN encoder output, flattened `(B*T, encoder_flatten_size)` |
| `fb` / `fb_t` | feedback vector `(B, fb_dim)` where `fb_dim=dz` (legacy default `num_classes + num_pos`) |
| `trans_ih` | input-hidden transformation `(B, H, input_size)` |
| `gate_ih` / `gate_hh` | sigmoid-gated weights |
| `outer_d` | rank-1 outer product for component d |
| `avg_outer_all` | accumulated average outer, shape `(n_comp, H, input_size)` |
| `activation_per_sample` | per-frame activation `(N, dim)` float32 |
| `sorted_npz_order` | index array mapping display order → original unit index |
| `channel_order` | index array for CNN feature channel reordering |

## CLI Arguments
Use the exact names from Section 3.3 of AGENT.md. Never invent synonyms
(e.g. do not use `--output` instead of `--save_dir`, or `--checkpoint` instead of `--ckpt`).
For `train_model.py`, CNN dropout sweep is **`--cnn_dropout`** (one or more floats, default `[0]`); middle-path dropout is **`--rnn_dropout`** (single float, default **0.5**). Checkpoint suffix: **`cdo`** = cnn, **`rdo`** = rnn.

## Checkpoint Filename Abbreviations
`h` = hidden_size, `lr` = learning rate, `wd` = weight_decay,
`cdo` = cnn_dropout, `rdo` = rnn_dropout, `dz` = GaWF feedback_dim, `fb` = fb_start_epoch, `acc` = use_acceleration,
`sector` / `coord` / `allchars` = label mode.

